comments.body:
Welcome to Angular.js and its cool module system :grin: 

There are two possibilities:

Make `constant.js` just return an object instead of registering the constants automatically:

``` javascript
// constants.js
module.exports = {
    'all': '*',
    'admin': 'ROLE_ADMIN',
    'user': 'ROLE_USER'
};

// app.js
myApp.constant('USER_ROLES', require('./constants.js'));
```

Or inject myApp to `constants.js`

``` javascript
// constants.js
module.exports = function (myApp) {
    myApp.constant('USER_ROLES', {
        'all': '*',
        'admin': 'ROLE_ADMIN',
        'user': 'ROLE_USER'
    });
};

// app.js
require('./constants.js')(myApp);
```

